result.title: 1987 - 1987 Centre for Environment, Fisheries & Aquaculture Science (Cefas) 1987 Eastern Irish Sea Groundfish Survey Catch Data - Silver Star Time Series
result.name: 1987-1987-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-1987-eastern-irish-sea-gro
result.notes:
A series of groundfish surveys were carried out on the fishing vessel Silver 
Star from 1976 to 1991 in the eastern Irish Sea. Fishing took place using a 
Boris Goshawk trawl towed for an hour. This data is from the 3 surveys carried 
out in 1987. Numbers at length by centimetre of the main commercial fish 
species are recorded. Station positions by area are recorded. A summary table 
is included for cruises 01/87, 02/87 and 03/87 containing catch data for all 
other species.
